rican film star  John Wayne  (  1907–79 )."]},{"name":"Marcia","meanings":["Often used as a feminine equivalent of   Mark  , but in fact a feminine form of <i>Marcius</i>, itself a derivative of   Marcus .  One  St Marcia  is commemorated in a group with Felix, Luciolus, Fortunatus, and others; another with Zenais, Cyria, and Valeria; and a third with Ariston, Crescentian, Eutychian, Urban, Vitalis, Justus, Felicissimus, Felix, and Symphorosa. None is individually very famous."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":17,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Mary de Ossory was born about 1242, in Bedingfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Domhnall de Ossory. She married Adam de Bedingfield II about 1263, in Bedingfield, Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. She died about 1267, in her hometown, at the age of 27."},"et":{"about 1242–about 1267":"umbes 1242–umbes 1267","1227–1289":"1227–1289","1242–1267":"1242–1267","1240–1275":"1240–1275","1264–1331":"1264–1331","1265–Male":"1265–Surnud","1266–Female":"1266–Surnud","1267–Female":"1267–Surnud","1205–1258":"1205–1258","1264":"1264","1275":"1275","1242":"1242","1240":"1240","1205":"1205","1227":"1227","1259":"1259","1258":"1258","1267":"1267","1289":"1289","1266":"1266","1265":"1265","1331":"1331","about 1267":"umbes 1267","about 1242":"umbes 1242","about 1264":"umbes 1264","about 1263":"umbes 1263","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Bedingfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Bedingfield, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bedingfield, Suffolk, England":"Bedingfield, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"about 1242–abou